    "body": "fix https://github.com/sgl-project/sglang/issues/5404\r\n\r\nBind the v2 merge_state kernel to the CUDA stream as the CUDA graph requires it.\r\n\r\n## w/o speculative decoding\r\n\r\n- cmd\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nMERGE_STATE_MODE=cuda python3 -m sglang.launch_server \\\r\n  --model $HF_MODELS/Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct \\\r\n  --trust-remote-code \\\r\n  --tp-size 1 \\\r\n  --mem-fraction-static 0.9 \\\r\n  --attention-backend flashinfer \\\r\n  --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8852 \\\r\n  --dtype bfloat16\r\n```\r\nto test merge_state v2 with flashinfer, please modify flashinfer_backend.py, like: (or you can checkout this debug branch https://github.com/vipshop/sglang/tree/fix-merge-state-cuda-graph-debug)\r\n\r\n```python\r\nfrom sgl_kernel import merge_state_v2\r\n\r\n# define merge_state_triton ......\r\n\r\nimport os\r\n\r\nMERGE_STATE_MODE = os.environ.get(\"MERGE_STATE_MODE\", \"cuda\").lower()\r\n\r\nprint(f\"MERGE_STATE_MODE: {MERGE_STATE_MODE}\")\r\nif MERGE_STATE_MODE == \"cuda\":\r\n    merge_state = merge_state_v2\r\nelse:\r\n    merge_state = merge_state_triton\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n- w/o this fix\r\n\r\n```bash\r\npython3 benchmark/gsm8k/bench_sglang.py \\\r\n  --port 8852 --num-shots 8 \\\r\n  --num-questions 128 \\\r\n  --parallel 16 \\\r\n  --data-path /workspace/dev/openllm/benchmarks/data/gsm8k/test.jsonl\r\n100%|███████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████| 128/128 [01:39<00:00,  1.29it/s]\r\nAccuracy: 0.000\r\nInvalid: 0.945\r\nLatency: 99.670 s\r\n```\r\nAccuracy is 0.000\r\n\r\n- w/ this fix\r\n\r\ncuda graph is enabled\r\n```bash\r\n[2025-04-15 19:51:49 TP0] Load weight end. type=LlamaForCausalLM, dtype=torch.bfloat16, avail mem=29.17 GB, mem usage=15.07 GB.\r\n[2025-04-15 19:51:49 TP0] KV Cache is allocated. #tokens: 202730, K size: 12.37 GB, V size: 12.37 GB\r\n[2025-04-15 19:51:49 TP0] Memory pool end. avail mem=3.38 GB\r\n2025-04-15 19:51:49,804 - INFO - flashinfer.jit: Prebuilt kernels not found, using JIT backend\r\nMERGE_STATE_MODE: cuda\r\n[2025-04-15 19:51:49 TP0] Capture cuda graph begin. This can take up to several minutes. avail mem=2.89 GB\r\nCapturing batches (avail_mem=2.79 GB):   0%|                                                                                                                       | 0/23 [00:00<?, ?it/s]2025-04-15 19:51:50,363 - INFO - flashinfer.jit: Loading JIT ops: batch_decode_with_kv_cache_dtype_q_bf16_dtype_kv_bf16_dtype_o_bf16_dtype_idx_i32_head_dim_qk_128_head_dim_vo_128_posenc_0_use_swa_False_use_logits_cap_False\r\n2025-04-15 19:51:50,391 - INFO - flashinfer.jit: Finished loading JIT ops: batch_decode_with_kv_cache_dtype_q_bf16_dtype_kv_bf16_dtype_o_bf16_dtype_idx_i32_head_dim_qk_128_head_dim_vo_128_posenc_0_use_swa_False_use_logits_cap_False\r\nCapturing batches (avail_mem=1.60 GB): 100%|██████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████| 23/23 [00:07<00:00,  3.13it/s]\r\n[2025-04-15 19:51:57 TP0] Capture cuda graph end. Time elapsed: 7.36 s. avail mem=1.59 GB. mem usage=1.30 GB.\r\n```\r\n\r\nbenchmark\r\n```bash\r\n python3 benchmark/gsm8k/bench_sglang.py \\\r\n  --port 8852 --num-shots 8 \\\r\n  --num-questions 128 \\\r\n  --parallel 16 \\\r\n  --data-path /workspace/dev/openllm/benchmarks/data/gsm8k/test.jsonl\r\n100%|███████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████| 128/128 [00:24<00:00,  5.15it/s]\r\nAccuracy: 0.781\r\nInvalid: 0.000\r\nLatency: 25.067 s\r\n```\r\nAccuracy is 0.781\r\n\r\n## w/ speculative decoding\r\n\r\n- cmd\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nMERGE_STATE_MODE=cuda python3 -m sglang.launch_server \\\r\n  --model $HF_MODELS/Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct \\\r\n  --speculative-algorithm EAGLE3 \\\r\n  --speculative-draft-model-path $HF_MODELS/sglang-EAGLE3-Llama-3.1-Instruct-8B \\\r\n  --speculative-num-steps 3 \\\r\n  --speculative-eagle-topk 2 \\\r\n  --speculative-num-draft-tokens 3 \\\r\n  --trust-remote-code \\\r\n  --tp-size 1 \\\r\n  --mem-fraction-static 0.75 \\\r\n  --attention-backend flashinfer \\\r\n  --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8852 \\\r\n  --dtype bfloat16\r\n```\r\n\r\n- w/ this fix\r\n```bash\r\npython3 benchmark/gsm8k/bench_sglang.py \\\r\n  --port 8852 --num-shots 8 \\\r\n  --num-questions 128 \\\r\n  --parallel 16 \\\r\n  --data-path /workspace/dev/openllm/benchmarks/data/gsm8k/test.jsonl\r\n100%|███████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████| 128/128 [00:21<00:00,  5.96it/s]\r\nAccuracy: 0.797\r\nInvalid: 0.000\r\nLatency: 21.499 s\r\nOutput throughput: 579.740 token/s\r\n```\r\n\r\nI have only conducted tests under the Ada architecture so far. Please carry out more tests on other architectures.",
